      AO (American Optical) Spencer Divided Circle Spectrometer (Spectroscope)

      Pricing & History

      • Sold for
        Start Free Trial or Sign In to see what it's worth.
      • Sold Date
      • Source eBay
      AO (American Optical) Spencer Divided Circle Spectrometer (Spectroscope)Serial number 2713. Date: some time after 1935, when AO purchased Spencer.This spectrometer is complete and in excellent mechanical, optical and cosmetic condition. The adjustable prism table is of unfinished brass and is NOT ORIGINAL.An inventory control sticker of the Virginia Military Institute is affixed.The auction includes:1. Equilateral dispersing prism. Absolutely pristine condition.2. An original copy of Spencer Spectrometer Manual by Roger S. Esty, in fine condition. Copyright 1938. 38 pages 5" X 7 ½"3. Custom fit plywood case, painted black, with handle and door latch. Not original. Sturdy, utilitarian, and in good condition; but hardly fine woodworking.Shipping: The total weight of the spectrometer plus the wooden box is 35 lbs. If you do not want the box let me know; that will reduce the shipping weight by 15 lbs.
